cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.NA 

This paper is primarily focused on image denoising, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques for minimizing the Stein's unbiased risk estimator (SURE), which is related to information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper proposes a fast and adaptive blockwise shrinkage algorithm, which involves matrix manipulation and computation, falling under the multimedia (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves evaluating the performance of various image denoising techniques, which can be considered a machine learning (cs.LG) problem.
